parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, vibrate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or vibrates when accelerating
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle fails to respond to the accelerator pedal
the transmission makes a loud whirring or banging sound
the vehicle shudders or judders when starting from a dead stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch in the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, vibrate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch engages late or hesitates
the vehicle jerks or vibrates when accelerating
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle fails to respond to the accelerator pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the bearing in the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to vibrate or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes when driving
the transmission makes a loud whirring or grinding sound.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid battery can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or stalls
the battery warning light is illuminated
the vehicle's fuel economy is degraded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injury or death, compromising the safety of the vehicle occupants.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
the vehicle is involved in an accident
and the airbag does not deploy despite the severity of the impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of an airbag can cause distraction, injury, or loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: The airbag deploys unexpectedly
the passenger-side seat airbag deploys without a crash
the airbag warning light illuminates
and the airbag deploys while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to receive recall notifications or incorrect information can lead to delayed or missed repairs, compromising vehicle safety and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The owner does not receive recall notifications
the recall notification is incorrect or incomplete
and the vehicle is not repaired despite the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctions in the airbag system can lead to false warnings, unintended deployments, or failure to deploy in a crash, compromising vehicle safety and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag system malfunctions
and the vehicle is involved in an accident with airbag deployment issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid battery can cause the vehicle to stop running, leaving the driver stranded, and can also lead to expensive repairs.
symptoms: The IMF light comes on
the battery needs to be replaced frequently
the vehicle stops running
the hybrid system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to disclose a salvage/rebuilt title can lead to the buyer being unaware of the vehicle's history, which can affect its reliability, safety, and resale value.
symptoms: The buyer is not informed about the salvage/rebuilt title
the title is held by the Department of Driver Services due to incorrect odometer readings
the buyer discovers the title is salvage/rebuilt when trying to insure the vehicle.
